fields.Title: CANAL / HAWTHORN
fields.Description: The hawthorn tree on Rue de Saint-Ghislaine. A reel of bronze magnetic tape is caught in its branches. It's a part of Egg Head's "make the music harder core" task. Interfacing White Check to get it.
fields.Placement:
Area: Plaza area, near canal?
Details: A tree on Rue de Saint-Gislaine with a reel of bronze magnetic tape is caught in it's branches.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Smooth move, operator." He looks t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Smooth move, operator." He looks to his wristwatch. "We done here?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Had enough assaulting *madre natur..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Had enough assaulting *madre natura*?" He looks at his wristwatch. "We should get moving."

fields.Title: Hawthorn Tree: "The hurt feelings of the tree are n..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The hurt feelings of the tree are not alleviated by this sudden display of care and emotion, you manipulative bastard.

fields.Title: You: ""Alright, tree. You got me, fair an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Alright, tree. You got me, fair and square. We're even, for now."

fields.Title: Jump to: [Hawthorn Tree: "The gnarled hawthorn tree on Rue de..."]
Interfacing: "Good idea. He might have the tools..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Good idea. He might have the tools -- the tape projector in the pawn shop uses similar tape...

fields.Title: Logic: "Maybe Roy from the pawnshop can hel..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Maybe Roy from the pawnshop can help you with this?

fields.Title: You: ""Good hawthorn." (Pat the tree.)"
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good hawthorn." (Pat the tree.)

fields.Title: Hawthorn Tree: "The hawthorn tree is not an inanima..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The hawthorn tree is not an inanimate object, it is a living thing. The thunk against the bark echoes with discontent.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Keep an eye on these trees. They're..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Keep an eye on these trees. They're up to no good.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yes. 'One day, grass will grow ove..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes. 'One day, grass will grow over our cities' and so on..." He looks at the tree. "Very poetic. Better not to dwell on it -- what with a murder to solve and all."

fields.Title: You: "God damn straight! Suck on that, *o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: God damn straight! Suck on that, *object*. My existence out-classes yours.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Trees likely do not understand the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Trees likely do not understand the concept of fairness. Better watch your back from now on...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant looks at you mumblin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant looks at you mumbling at the tree, then at his wristwatch. "Maybe we should get back to the case."

fields.Title: You: "Disentangle the tape."
fields.Dialogue Text: Disentangle the tape.

fields.Title: Hawthorn Tree: "The younger stems and branches are..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The younger stems and branches are adorned with sharp thorns that scratch your hand.

fields.Title: You: "I thought it would be cool, but ins..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I thought it would be cool, but instead all the violence made me feel sad and hollow...

fields.Title: Jump to: [Hawthorn Tree: "The gnarled hawthorn tree on Rue de..."]
Hawthorn Tree: "The tree looks by, in silence. No d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The tree looks by, in silence. No doubt plotting its next move against humanity. The bronze-coloured tape twists around its branches.
fields.Alternate1: The tree looks by in silence. No doubt plotting its next move against humanity.

fields.Title: You: ""He has to -- he's the Master of Ce..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He has to -- he's the Master of Ceremonies after all."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""You could also get it fixed at the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You could also get it fixed at the pawnshop across the street -- we shouldn't waste our time." He looks at his wristwatch a little impatiently.

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "At first the destructive urge felt..."
fields.Dialogue Text: At first the destructive urge felt exhilarating, as if it added something to your persona... but the feeling swiftly receded, leaving you with a sad emptiness.

fields.Title: You: ""What the fuck, tree?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What the fuck, tree?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Alright." Looks like the lieutenan..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Alright." Looks like the lieutenant doesn't really know what that means. "You could also get it fixed at the pawnshop across the street -- we shouldn't waste our time."

fields.Title: Jump to: [Hawthorn Tree: "The gnarled hawthorn tree on Rue de..."]
Inland Empire: "Shhhh! You shouldn't say it out lou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Shhhh! You shouldn't say it out loud... they'll realize you know!

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "There's a twisted logic in this mes..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's a twisted logic in this mess... you see the ends of the ribbon, the way it flows, how it twists and turns... it's all starting to make sense. It'll be easier to remove now.

fields.Title: You: "Ignore thought."
fields.Dialogue Text: Ignore thought.

fields.Title: Jump to: [Hawthorn Tree: "The gnarled hawthorn tree on Rue de..."]
Interfacing: "You just can't get it loose. All yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You just can't get it loose. All you've done is make your fingers bleed from the thorns.

fields.Title: Jump to: [Hawthorn Tree: "The gnarled hawthorn tree on Rue de..."]
Physical Instrument: "You tree-hugging pansy!"
fields.Dialogue Text: You tree-hugging pansy!

fields.Title: You: ""I'd think at least one of the rave..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'd think at least one of the ravers would know how to fix a broken tape if they want to set up a nightclub."

fields.Title: You: ""I'm not sure, but I'll find out. M..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm not sure, but I'll find out. Maybe Egg Head can point me in the right direction."

fields.Title: Interfacing: "With slow and deliberate motions, p..."
fields.Dialogue Text: With slow and deliberate motions, pulling, bending and unravelling -- you manage to extricate the magnetic tape from the branches.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "It curls up into a mess inside your..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It curls up into a mess inside your pocket. If only you could find a way to re-spool it, so that you could hear what's on the tape...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "He looks at his wristwatch a little..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He looks at his wristwatch a little impatiently. "You know, since tape-spinning isn't really our day job. Solving murder investigations is."

fields.Title: You: ""It's for Egg Head. I promised to m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's for Egg Head. I promised to make his van Eyck's jam hit a bit harder. Maybe this tape can help."

fields.Title: Hawthorn Tree: "Patting the tree reveals a small st..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Patting the tree reveals a small sticker which has almost been worn to oblivion. It reads: "RCM Emergencies Desk No. 8-100-2". Underneath, a slogan: "Mankind, be vigilant!"

fields.Title: Hawthorn Tree: "The hawthorn tree is disappointed b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The hawthorn tree is disappointed by your betrayal and psychopathic tendencies. Also, your fist hurts. A little.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The bronze ribbon twists around and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The bronze ribbon twists around and within the branches in an intricately natural pattern... but there's something...

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Oh, whatever. This barely registers..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Oh, whatever. This barely registers as damage.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""This is part of your church-thing,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is part of your church-thing, isn't it? Of course it is. It's too broken to play, you understand, right? It's not like Egg Head and his friends know how to fix it."

fields.Title: You: ""Piss off, nature!" (Punch the tree..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Piss off, nature!" (Punch the tree.)

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "The pain, it is nothing! Revel in i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The pain, it is nothing! Revel in it! Absorb it! Gain power from it!

fields.Title: Shivers: "Just like promised... You've stood..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Just like promised... You've stood here for what seem like aeons, guzzling the sickly fumes of lorries and carriages.

fields.Title: You: ""My god, nature is plotting an upri..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "My god, nature is plotting an uprising against us?"

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "It was a retaliation for your earli..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It was a retaliation for your earlier assault... the trees... are they plotting something?

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Yes. Beat yourself up for it. Good...."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes. Beat yourself up for it. Good. Everyone must suffer. You, the tree, everyone.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""You put your hand on a tree with s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You put your hand on a tree with sharp thorns, what did you think was going to happen?"

fields.Title: Hawthorn Tree: "The gnarled hawthorn tree on Rue de..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The gnarled hawthorn tree on Rue de Saint-Ghislaine. A wintry breeze blows by, making the magnetic tape flutter.
fields.Alternate1: The gnarled hawthorn tree on Rue de Saint-Ghislaine endures the wintry gusts with ease.

fields.Title: You: "Say nothing."
fields.Dialogue Text: Say nothing.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Yes, your pain is real. The pain of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes, your pain is real. The pain of a tree is mute and base and uninteresting.

fields.Title: Endurance: "A little? It's awful! The pain surg..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A little? It's awful! The pain surges through your knuckles and then lingers there... slowly pulsating, reminding you of your mistake.

fields.Title: Hawthorn Tree: "The hawthorn tree on Rue de Saint-G..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The hawthorn tree on Rue de Saint-Ghislaine. Bronze-coloured ribbons of magnetic tape are caught in its branches, fluttering in the breeze.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "Like an immaculate labyrinth, the m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Like an immaculate labyrinth, the magnetic tape twists and turns around the branches...

fields.Title: You: "What do I see?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What do I see?

fields.Title: You: ""I'm too embarrassed to say.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm too embarrassed to say."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant looks at the mess in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant looks at the mess in your hands. Only after you've successfully cleaned up the branches does the curiosity get him: "What's the tape for?" he asks.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""How? It's broken and unspooled. Do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "How? It's broken and unspooled. Do you think your new buddy knows how to fix it?"
